<TEXT>
americans say pete rose deserves a place in two 
venerable institutions the federal prison system and the baseball 
hall of fame 
eightyone percent in a national associated press poll said it 
was right for rose baseballs alltime hit leader to be sentenced 
to federal prison last week he got a fivemonth term last week for 
cheating on his taxes 
at the same time a majority said rose should be allowed to work 
in baseball again even though he was banished from the sport for 
gambling last year and twothirds said he deserved election to the 
hall of fame 
most respondents also said roses problems did little to damage 
his sport fiftysix percent said he had not hurt baseballs image 
and among those who said he had done damage only about a third 
said it was serious 
rose 49 exmanager of the cincinnati reds can apply for 
reinstatement to baseball and 63 percent said he should get it at 
some point 
rose becomes eligible in december 1991 for election by sports 
writers to the hall of fame with 4256 hits in a 24year career 
he was virtually assured of the honor before he ran afoul of the 
baseball commissioner and the law his chances now are less certain 
the poll did not specify an election date for rose asking only 
if he should be named to the hall of fame at some point 
baseball fans were a bit more likely than nonfans to favor him for 
the hall 71 to 63 percent and men were more supportive than 
women 74 to 62 percent 
women also were slightly more likely than men to say rose had 
damaged baseballs image 43 to 36 percent but men were a bit 
harder on rose in other areas they were more likely than women to 
say he deserved jail time 8578 percent and while 67 percent of 
women said rose should be allowed back into baseball at some point 
that fell to 59 percent of men 
in most cases opinion was roughly the same among respondents 
who called themselves baseball fans as among nonfans fiftyfour 
percent said they were fans 61 percent of the men and 48 percent 
of the women 
the telephone survey of 1004 adults was conducted for the ap 
from friday through tuesday by icr survey research group of media 
pa part of aus consultant cos the poll has a margin of error of 
plus or minus three percentage points 
</TEXT>
