<TEXT>
israel has ordered its stateowned el al 
airline to halt its twiceweekly flights to stockholm in response 
to changes in swedens airport security arrangements 
the new security procedures made by the government of sweden 
do not answer the security requirements of the government of 
israel yehiel amitai spokesman for the ministry of 
transportation said wednesday 
he would not say what changes had been made but said his 
ministry could not allow the continuation of el al flights that 
were not adequately guarded amitai said the decision would be 
reversed if sweden returned to the previous security arrangements 
the transportation ministry citing the principle of mutuality 
also banned all charter flights originating in sweden from landing 
in israel the scandinavian carrier sas does not operate regular 
flights from stockholm to israel 
el al has canceled its flights in the past over security 
arrangements usually it involves the presence of israeli security 
people who want direct responsibility for the safety of the 
aircraft and passengers something not every country is willing to 
allow 
el al flights are considered prime targets for palestinian 
guerrillas and security is very stringent 
in december 1985 guerrillas of the radical abu nidal 
organization launched attacks against the el al counters in the 
rome and vienna airports killing 16 people 
</TEXT>
