an experiment in putting british bobbies on bikes 
to fight crime has ended successfully in the northern england town 
of sheffield police said 
plainclothes officers spent two weeks cycling the streets and 
arrested more than a dozen car thieves in sheffield 145 miles 
northwest of london 
at first i was a bit skeptical but it has been an unqualified 
success south yorkshire police superintendent peter hale said 
wednesday 
hale said the force was considering ordering more of the 18gear 
mountain bikes for other officers 
