<TEXT>
guerrillas fired two rocketpropelled grenades 
at the presidential palace late wednesday less than three days 
before presidentelect alberto fujimori is to take office police 
said damage to the palace in downtown lima was minor 
the attack took place just after outgoing president alan garcia 
met with a group of judges to sign a law reforming perus 
judiciary police and witnesses said 
one grenade exploded against the rear wall of the building and 
the other exploded on the roof 
the grenades were launched by two men from next to a small car 
parked 100 yards from the palaces rear entry the men then fled in 
the car police said 
afterwards in comments to reporters garcia discounted the 
importance of the attack 
all they prove with their pistols and bombs is that theyre 
psychologically inferior they have to resort to violence because 
they cannot convince people through politics he said 
police set up roadblocks throughout downtown lima and detained 
hundreds of people they said they were unsure which of perus two 
rebel groups staged the attack the maoist shining path or the 
procuban tupac amaru 
in other attacks late wednesday shining path rebels burned a 
cityowned bus in a poor lima neighborhood in another poor area of 
the capital rebels from the same group bombed a telephone 
exchange causing moderate damage 
the shining path has conducted a violent campaign against perus 
government throughout the last decade 
