soviet union and says he learned there that communism doesnt work 
he can make a good case that it hasnt worked well for district 
12 
the district has no kindergarten no schools ganbold said 
the electricity stops sometimes there is no telephone in the 
district 
ganbold said he has cannot promise that he could provide the 
services the district lacks but can vow to give the problems more 
attention 
he admits his campaign got off to a slow start he didnt begin 
doortodoor visits until wednesday but he said ochirbat still 
hasnt campaigned in person sending high party officials instead 
at a news conference tuesday ochirbat said some communist party 
members criticized the districts communists for not campaigning 
harder on his behalf but he did not announce any plans for taking 
a more active role 
nor did he outline any program for helping the district saying 
only that his party was now firmly on the path of reform 
