maglev trains are propelled by magnets on a cushion of air over 
a rail such trains could travel up to 300 miles per hour use less 
energy than conventional transportation modes and would be cheaper 
to ride than airplanes according to the report 
so far only the japanese and the germans have developed 
prototype maglev trains but several projects are under discussion 
in the united states 
maglev was invented and pioneered in the 1960s and 1970s by 
americans including james powell and gordon danby at brookhaven 
national laboratory on long island but us advances stopped 
around 1974 when the federal role in maglev development ended 
moynihan said at a news conference 
