sighed and said not in this century i can see going into the 
year 2000 with some pending litigation of some sort 
hazelwood said he thought his experience might drive other 
tanker captains out of the business 
everything in your private life is paraded in public and 
youre lampooned from pillar to post is the job worth it i still 
havent made up my mind a lot of good people will leave the field 
rather than risk this 
hazelwood said he had pondered going into some other field 
perhaps even law given his exposure to it as he waits nine months 
to be eligible to reclaim his captains license issued in 1966 
