secretarygeneral javier perez de cuellar and will comprise as 
many agents as are necessary 
the mission will enjoy broad powers to adopt any initiative it 
deems appropriate for the promotion and defense of human rights 
said a joint communique 
it said the mission will be free to document and denounce rights 
violations conduct unrestricted interviews with all people make 
recommendations to both the government and guerrillas and publish 
its reports conclusions and recommendations 
the mission is to begin work as soon as a ceasefire is reached 
