rebels modify their positions in order to meet a september target 
date for a ceasefire 
but the insurgents insist that accords on military issues 
including a purge of rights abusers from the officer corps an end 
to military impunity and drastic reduction of troop strength be 
reached prior to halting combat rebel chiefs say a september 
ceasefire may be unrealistic 
a joint communique said the military issue would receive 
priority consideration at the next round of talks scheduled 
aug 1722 in san jose 
