<TEXT>
five months after agreeing with president bush 
on lofty goals to produce an american renaissance in education 
the nations governors meet this weekend to decide who will oversee 
the task and how to assess students progress toward that target 
the governors traveling to mobile ala for the 82nd annual 
meeting of the national governors association hope to agree on 
the makeup of a bipartisan commission and its role in evaluating 
progress in reaching the six national education goals 
the governors also intend to decide how students should be 
tested and which learning skills should be measured 
while discussions began soon after the goals were outlined mike 
cohen of the governors association said this week a consensus 
still has not been reached on many details 
theres no horrible impasse said an association official 
