agree on a lot of things 
at stake are the goals bush set forth in his state of the union 
address in january the governors who met with the president last 
fall in an education summit gave their approval to the goals a 
month later 
besides making american students first in the world in math 
and science by the year 2000 the goals call for improving 
student competence in english history and geography increasing 
the high school graduation rate to at least 90 percent upgrading 
early childhood education improving adult literacy and freeing 
schools of violence and drugs 
the nations state school officers called on the governors and 
the president to adopt an eightstep set program of national 
