would link student performance with what the nation expects them to 
know and be able to do 
the governors are leaning toward organizing the commission along 
three tiers 
they would include a policysteering group possibly made up of 
governors to oversee the student assessment process an advisory 
group of highlevel education specialists and business officials 
and a staff to carry out the advisory groups recommendations 
perhaps more contentious will be determining a way to measure 
student success in achieving the national goals 
most states test students on their general academic knowledge 
but decades of widely reported dismal results have forced educators 
to reassess the most commonly used testing and assessment methods 
even within the bush administration there is disagreement on 
the meaning of standardized test scores education secretary lauro 
