multiplechoice tests are proof of students ability to use the 
language effectively in life and in learning the group said 
if not standardized tests what 
several states are experimenting with innovative testing methods 
most of which have been lumped under the category 
performancebased testing such assessments can include 
teachers evaluations of students work based on collections of 
their essays poems and drawings 
michigan illinois california and connecticut have been leaders 
in this movement said lawrence rudner of the education 
departments educational resources information center 
florida has a fiveyear plan to phase out standardized tests 
the concept is that standardized multiplechoice tests are 
limited because of the breadth and depth of what they can test 
rudner said students also need to be tested on how well they work 
in groups and on their problemsolving abilities for example 
the american federation of teachers has called for phasing out 
standardized multiplechoice tests and replacing them with 
reliable valid and educationally appropriate alternatives 
aft president shanker said performancebased assessments more 
accurately depict the status of american education than 
standardized tests 
a harsh critic of all assessment methods is albuquerque nm 
physician john jacob cannell leader of friends for education a 
nonprofit citizens group 
performancebased assessment is another form of cheating 
cannell said in an interview 
he contends that 83 percent of 5143 elementary school districts 
and 73 percent of 4501 secondary districts report standardized 
achievement test scores above national norms as do 48 of the 50 
states 
in an honest test he said half the states would be below 
average instead of having all of them claim to be above and by 
being below the national average then schools would be forced to 
spend extra money and admit that they are failing 
cannell contended that many teachers and principals now coach 
students on test questions give students more than the allotted 
time to take tests and even alter answer sheets to raise scores 
