the bill prohibits discrimination against the disabled in 
employment public accommodations transportation and 
telecommunications and defines as disabled anyone who has a mental 
or physical impairment limiting some major life function 
the disabilities bill like other major civil rights 
legislation includes a variety of sanctions for violators 
including those who discriminate in hiring it allows victims of 
employment discrimination to seek back pay reinstatement and 
attorneys fees however the law exempts businesses with fewer 
than 15 employees from the hiring provisions 
the measure includes new protection for aidsinfected workers 
this day belongs to you bush told the audience gathered 
outside the white house it was one of the largest billsigning 
ceremonies ever held at the white house 
