camp uniforms 
havels comments in the opening ceremony were made in the 
context of changes in eastern europe over the past year that 
instituted democracy while he never mentioned waldheims name 
some of the language appeared clearly directed at the austrian 
president who sat stonefaced in the first row 
the expectation that one can negotiate his way through history 
without punishment and be able to rewrite his own biography is part 
of the traditional madness of middle europe said havel 
whoever tries to do this hurts himself and his fellow citizens 
waldheim a former un secretarygeneral drew international 
criticism for concealing his service as an intelligence officer 
with a nazi army unit implicated in atrocities in yugoslavia and 
greece during world war ii he has denied wrongdoing 
since his election in 1986 waldheim has been shunned by most 
western nations including the united states 
this month cypriot president georgios vassiliou became the 
first western head of state to make an official visit to austria 
since waldheims election pope john paul ii met with waldheim in 
1987 
heinz galinski head of the german jewish council said last 
week he was shocked over weizsaeckers meeting with waldheim 
weiss in a statement tuesday condemned both waldheim and 
weizsaecker we view the meeting of havel and weizsaecker with 
waldheim as obscene and we will be raising a voice of moral 
conscience against waldheim who is an unrepentant nazi the 
rabbi said 
we especially are outraged that at a time of german 
reunification the president of west germany is meeting with 
waldheim the only way germany can move forward is to reject people 
like waldheim weiss said 
i am attending a cultural event as a private person havel 
said in an interview published wednesday by the salzburger 
nachrichten newspaper 
however at the time of the visit i am also president that 
is something one cannot discard that is to say something official 
remains attached to any of my visits 
while havel criticized western leaders for continuing to steer 
clear of waldheim he made it plain he was unlikely to make a state 
visit to austria as long as waldheim is president waldheims term 
is to expire in 1992 
