<TEXT>
tropical storm arthur weakened today as it moved 
slowly through the caribbean sea its winds dropping from 
nearhurricane strength of 70 mph to 50 mph the national hurricane 
center said 
a tropical storm watch remained for the southern coasts of haiti 
and the dominican republic but the storm was on a track that made 
it less of a threat to hispaniola the island shared by the two 
countries forecasters said 
at noon edt arthurs top sustained winds of 50 mph well below 
the 74 mph minimumhurricane strength were centered near latitude 
153 north and longitude 690 west or about 230 miles 
southsoutheast of santo domingo dominican republic 
it was moving westnorthwest at 20 and was expected to continue 
that motion through the day said hal gerrish a hurricane 
specialist at the center in suburban coral gables 
some further decrease in strength is likely during the next 24 
hours he said 
storm warnings for trinidad tobago grenada and grenada 
dependencies were discontinued wednesday after the storm passed 
through from the atlantic 
grenada reported winds gusting to 55 mph early wednesday when 
the center of arthur passed over the island and heavy rains were 
reported on tobago and other islands in the area said bob sheets 
director of the hurricane center 
arthur the 1990 atlantic hurricane seasons first named storm 
grew from a depression the second of the 1990 season that formed 
sunday in the open atlantic the hurricane season runs from june 1 
to nov 30 
