<TEXT>
the nations communist party 
chairman defended himself and his party thursday before irate 
voters who demanded to know the truth behind purges and coverups 
over seven decades of authoritarian rule 
i didnt repress anybody the whitehaired dignified 
gombojavyn ochirbat told about 200 people from ulan bators 12th 
election district where he is running for a seat in the national 
legislature 
the contest has become the most dramatic one in the first 
multiparty elections ever held in this longisolated sovietbloc 
nation 
it pits the 61yearold ochirbat a longtime party official who 
stresses moderation against a 29yearold lawyer with no political 
experience who favors bold moves toward democracy and economic 
privatization 
on sunday the districts approximately 5000 voters will decide 
whether ochirbat arguably the most powerful man in mongolia by 
virtue of his party post should also sit in the 430seat 
legislature the great peoples hural 
the communist party in mongolia is already going down not 
just the organization but the theory of communism said 
ochirbats opponent ganbold of the recently formed party of 
national progress i decided it would be appropriate not to allow 
the head of the communist party to be a deputy 
ochirbat became party chief in march when street protests 
inspired by eastern europes anticommunist revolution forced 
mongolias top communists to resign he has overseen the countrys 
first tentative steps toward democracy but insists it should 
remain socialist 
on thursday he shared a podium with ganbold as district 12 held 
a freewheeling meetthecandidates night that would have been 
unheard of not long ago 
residents of the impoverished shanty district on ulan bators 
western fringe eagerly called out questions about past purges a 
recent scandal involving a public prosecutor rumored price 
increases and restrictions on emigration 
in the past the communist party made many mistakes 
ochirbat said speaking calmly but firmly but we shouldnt just 
accuse the party of mistakes it also has done good things 
my father also was repressed he added in 1932 he was 
arrested with a couple of friends i know history quite well but 
we should understand the situation of that time 
ganbolds party of national progress has said it is running in 
part against ochirbats record as a ranking official of the past 
stalinist regime he was in charge of party ideology during the 
1960s when a group of intellectuals were purged but ochirbat said 
he was not involved 
speaking about another 1960s purge of two party officials 
accused of being prochinese he said everybody believed they 
were enemies of the people i was young then i believed it too 
but now according to the archival materials we can certainly say 
this was a fabricated case 
afterward local residents said the contest would be close 
its very democratic said dorj rolling a cigarette outside 
the tiny meeting hall i think ill vote for the communists but 
i also support the democrats because they put forward the most 
interesting proposals 
most of the opposition parties have joined in what is called a 
democratic coalition to back key candidates such as ganbold 
in sundays primary ochirbat led with more than 2500 votes to 
ganbolds more than 1300 according to partial official figures 
but opposition candidates altogether won nearly as much as ochirbat 
showing that he is not invincible with just the two competing in 
the second round ganbolds party believes he has a chance 
most young people support ganbold said a local backer 
turtoghokh 
ganbold began campaigning doortodoor wednesday a bit late 
he admitted but in an interview wednesday night he said he was 
warmly received 
one of my fears that older people would be against me 
disappeared today as i met a lot of older people who said they 
were willing to back me he said 
ganbold a juniorlevel officer in the ministry of law and 
jurisdiction said he knew hard times as a child as his mother 
struggled to raise five children by herself he said he can relate 
to the problems of district 12s residents 
the district has no kindergarten no schools ganbold said 
to go shopping they have to go two bus stops even the 
electricity stops sometimes there is no telephone 
the lesson he said is that communism doesnt work communism 
is a foreign idea to mongolia that is why a lot of communist party 
members do not back it ideologically they just belong 
but while meeting the voters he softpedaled his ideological 
attacks and kept his promises moderate 
if elected i will try to solve at least one of the smallest 
things ive promised he said 
