more than 8 million americans more than half 
of them elderly need help with at least one daily activity because 
of a health problem according to a census bureau report released 
thursday 
about 16 percent of the population that is 65 and older needed 
help with household chores meal preparation or personal hygiene 
according to the 1986 census survey which is the latest data 
available 
these senior citizens make up about 54 percent of the total 
number of americans 15 and older who need assistance to perform at 
least one everyday activity the rest are under age 65 
about 56 million of those needing assistance lived with a 
family while 23 million lived alone and 300000 lived with 
nonrelatives according to the survey 
the survey also found that 58 million people over age 15 were 
providing care to a household member and about a quarter of these 
caregivers were 65 or older 
more than 15 million people were helping people outside their 
household 
