east germany on thursday jailed the former 
chief of the communist secret police on suspicion he had hidden 
some of the worlds most notorious terrorists 
however officials said deposed communist leader erich honecker 
was too sick to prosecute on allegations of abuse of office and 
corruption 
authorities arrested 82yearold erich mielke who ran the 
sprawling foreign and domestic spy network that touched nearly 
every east german and bolstered honeckers 19 years of ironfisted 
rule 
mielke was held pending investigation of charges he abused his 
power jailed people for criticizing the old regime and turned 
east germany into a haven for leftwing terrorists linked to some 
of the most spectacular attacks of the past two decades 
the government said even though the allegations against honecker 
would justify a similar criminal investigation the 77yearold 
former leaders health is too precarious he is suffering from 
kidney cancer at a soviet military hospital outside berlin 
some leaders of the ousted regime were arrested late last year 
or early this year but were freed because of poor health or 
advanced age 
