<TEXT>
supreme court nominee david souter brushed 
aside questions thursday about a letter he wrote nearly a decade 
ago opposing legislation that would have forced judges to make 
decisions on abortions for teenagers 
souter making a round of courtesy calls in the senate told 
reporters he would disclose what is constitutionally 
appropriate at his confirmation hearings 
meanwhile one of the justices he will join if confirmed 
thurgood marshall said hed never heard of souter before he was 
