was already blown by congress when he later sold the rights to 
his story for 10000 to cbs 
beckman referred to the hostilities as a war to bolster the 
defense contention that hasenfus and sawyer had willingly accepted 
the risks when they signed on 
it wasnt a war and vietnam wasnt a war hasenfus 
responded 
under questioning by secords attorney thomas spencer hasenfus 
agreed he had never met the man he was suing nor did he have any 
documents signed by secord 
hasenfus also acknowledged he had received some money after the 
crashhe said a brown bag containing 6000 was given to his wife 
by a man who said this is from the boys 
