presence of us chemical weapons on german soil was widely 
assumed washington refused to acknowledge their exact location 
until march 
the west german government is paying 31 million for removal of 
the chemical weapons and the us cost is 52 million 
the artillery shells some 6 inches in diameter some 8 inches 
are loaded with liquid nerve agents us military officials 
said they were brought to clausen between 1958 and 1968 where 
they have remained ever since 
one convoy will take the weapons daily from clausen to miesau 
over the next 30 days the rail transport to the north sea port 
will take about a week and will be conducted at night 
