of its owner birgit lenderink who lives in a buddhist meditation 
center in barnet vt 
the governments case entitled united states of america vs 
one obscene photograph drew fire from artists as well as 
newspaper editorial writers who noted that the photograph was 
exhibited in many galleries and reprinted in a harper amp row book on 
american nude photography 
cohens statement also cited the ready availability of this 
photograph in other parts of the country 
federal officials seized the framed black and white print this 
winter at the state line in houlton as friends were trying to bring 
it to ms lenderink 
none of the people who made or possessed the picture were 
charged in the case 
chappell who lives in el rito nm a tiny farming community 
north of santa fe did not respond to messages left at his home by 
the associated press 
maine arts commission spokesman dick dyer said he understood how 
someone unfamiliar with chappells work could question the 
photograph 
when he cohen saw the image without any explanation 
whatsoever to his credit he did investigate said dyer were 
very pleased that he has had the wisdom to see through the process 
and decide not to prosecute the photograph 
the case was withdrawn from us district court in bangor 
