could spill over into the premiers talks north korean radio 
blasted south korea for poking their nose into the rally and 
laying artificial hurdles to foil 
the 19point agreement for prime ministers talks calls for the 
two sides to meet in seoul sept 47 and again in the norths 
capital of pyongyang oct 1619 
by signing the accord north koreas communist government 
granted tacit recognition to the legitimacy of the seoul government 
for the first time since separate governments were formed in 1948 
this precious fruit will open a decisive chapter in a road to 
ending national division and achieving peaceful unification said 
south korean chief delegate song hanho 
songs north korean counterpart paik said the agreement will 
open a new chapter in the history of the national division 
the two prime ministers kang younghoon of south korea and yon 
hyung muk of north korea are ceremonial figureheads with little 
policymaking roles but their meeting would be symbolically 
significant as they would be the highestranking officials of the 
rival states to ever meet 
the outcome of the rally and the prime ministers talks are seen 
as a gauge of future korean relations 
the rally would mark the first contact between civilian 
organizations of the two koreas in the past south korean 
authorities have blocked such contacts out of fear they could turn 
into radical antiseoul protests 
proposed sites for the rally include the capitals of either 
north or south korea or panmunjom the aug 15 date is the 45th 
anniversary of the liberation of korea from japanese colonial rule 
and is a sentimental holiday on both sides of the border 
