<TEXT>
more than 10 japanese securities companies are 
being investigated for allegedly compensating favored customers for 
16 billion yen or 107 million in losses following the 1987 stock 
market crash major japanese newspapers reported thursday 
the reports which came out in the early afternoon thursday 
appeared to have an immediate impact on tokyo currency and stock 
markets stimulating a fall in both the yen and in share prices 
yamaichi securities co daiwa securities co and about 10 other 
brokerage firms were said to have compensated favored clients after 
the oct 20 crash in which the benchmark nikkei stock average fell 
149 percent the largest daily fall on the tokyo exchange 
the reports were attributed to an investigation by the tokyo tax 
administration which refused to comment 
the securities companies allegedly sold warrants convertible 
bonds and other market instruments at bargain prices to special 
institutional and individual clients who later sold them back to 
the brokers at market rates for a profit the reports said 
the companies then recorded the sums used for repurchasing the 
bonds as losses and deducted them from their taxes in fiscal 1987 
the reports said that the tokyo tax administration has been 
reviewing such transactions and planned to assess the companies a 
total of 7 billion yen or 466 million in additional taxes 
the administration reportedly views such writeoffs as 
contributions or entertainment fees which are therefore taxable 
they said 
among the companies named yamaichi securities was said to have 
compensated clients for the largest amount of losses of up to 8 
billion yen or 533 million 
in a statement masazumi konichi a senior yamaichi official 
said tax authorities had already completed their review of yamaichi 
financil proceedings during 1987 
we understand that all bond transactions that took place 
during that time were fair transactions there is no truth in the 
reports of loss compensation he said 
the release of the report which appeared in the evening edition 
of each of japans major national newspapers had a major impact on 
tokyo financial markets 
the dollar closed higher at 15011 yen up 098 yen from 
wednesdays finish of 14913 yen on the stock market the nikkei 
stock average of 225 selected issues lost 33152 points or 105 
percent closing at 3136975 
the news of made many market players lose confidence said 
yozo asai an analyst with yamaichi 
