the boeing co on thursday reported record 
secondquarter profits double those of a year earlier saying its 
soaring commercial jet sales and healthier profit margins offset 
major losses in its defense business 
boeing the worlds largest manufacturer of commercial aircraft 
had profits of 387 million or 112 a share for the quarter 
ended june 30 thats up 985 percent from the 195 million or 57 
cents a share in secondquarter 1989 sales were up 374 percent 
from 507 billion to 697 billion 
frank shrontz boeing chairman and chief executive officer 
attributed the profit growth to higher commercial aircraft sales 
and operating margins 
boeing has had five consecutive years of record jetliner orders 
which are now translating into record sales all seven of its 
current aircraft models also are well into production and past the 
expensive development and startup phases the company has steadily 
boosted its production to where it now averages better than one 
plane a day 
