<TEXT>
donald c carter the takeover specialist who 
pleaded guilty to stealing 1 million from clients in march was 
sentenced to 16 months to four years in state prison 
carter 41 was also ordered to pay a 50000 fine and put 1 
million in a fund to compensate his victims acting new york 
supreme court justice george f roberts handed down the sentence 
wednesday 
the firm carter started in 1974 the carter organization agreed 
to forfeit 1 million to new york state which will make it 
available to those who can prove they were defrauded 
carter sold the firm now doing business as quorum 
communications inc to the vpi group plc a british public 
relations firm in 1987 for 76 million 
ronald goldstock director of the new york state organized crime 
task force which headed the carter investigation said that 
between 1984 and 1989 carter routinely billed his clients for 
nonexistent or inflated expenses when questioned about the 
expenses carter supplied fraudulent documentation to justify them 
goldstock said 
the corporate clients he was said to have defrauded included 
union carbide corp shell oil caesars world inc unum an 
insurance company and macandrews amp forbes group inc which owns 
the revlon cosmetics company 
carter pleaded guilty march 20 to grand larceny and filing a 
false and fradulent personal income tax return 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

